detailedReviews.author: Alex Czernik
detailedReviews.text:
Update: Placed a large over $100 order for pick up expecting the same quality as before. Night and day difference. The quality of the dishes across the board were poor. The stir fry was soggy and too much sauce. The Paid Tai was dry with over cooked chicken. The rocket shrimp were ok. The soups we had tasted good but lacked a great deal of ingrediencies. Seems like something drastic has changed at this restaurant and we will not be back. Pity because it was our favorite. Too expensive for low quality food.

We placed a take-out order via the chow now app. on Thursday for pick up at 4:45. The first thing I noticed was that the prices on the app were the same as on the web site, no mark up! I missed the spot to enter the coupon code so my bad. The food was ready when requested. The staff was very nice and the place was very clean. As we were getting ready to leave the owner came running out with our fried rice which they forgot to give us. Good catch. That never happens. We ordered Rocket Shrimps and Tom Yum Gai soup for appetizers and we ordered chicken pad tai and beef and broccoli wok dish for entrees. All the food was excellent, very hot and flavorful. I think we have found our new go to for Asian food!

detailedReviews.author: Zachary Bagdon
detailedReviews.text: Simply the best Thai food in the tri-state area.   Their Massaman Curry is amazing, and I eat there at least once a week for lunch.  Prices are very good for the quantity and quality.  Service is always with a smile.  Go a few times, and they will treat you like family.   The ability to change the spiciness of every menu item allows a variation of your favorite dish from week to week.  Be cautious, as Thai hot can be exceedingly spicy, depending on the type of peppers they use.  Unlike other restaurants, spiciness does not cover up the flavor, but enhances it.  I highly recommend Soybean to anyone looking for a delicious Thai meal.  In addition, they do very well with food allergies, especially gluten.
